obo:ECO_0006062  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2446  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The work utilizes vGlut pHluorin in neurons deficient in alpha, beta and gamma synuclein to establish a deficit in the rate of synaptic vesicle endocytosis (figure 1a). Measuring the stimulation dependent appearance of cell surface fluorescence (exocytosis) and disappearance (endocytosis) shows a selective deficit in endocytosis (Figure 1f-h). Systematically rescuing against this defect with the heterologous expression of the individual alpha, beta and gamma synucleins identifies that each are independently capable of fully performing this function (Figure 2 b).\n\n19/01/2018 Pim\n- The experiments use a triple KO animal combined with re-expression rescue experiments.\n- I have not created the equivalent annotation for gamma synuclein since its presence in the presynaptic terminal has not been established.. Experimental description: Material and methods. Mice. Generation and characterization of synuclein null..................\nFigure 2......................neurons transfected with mouse alpha-syn..................." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2446" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

